festival.introText:
We have gone bigger and better than ever before with this year's explosive Wile Out Festival in Burnley’s Towneley Park. It has a vast line-up of international DJ talent from the worlds of house, tech-house, bass, and drum & bass. There is no other festival quite like this in the region.

The location for this unmissable one day getaway is Towneley Park, a beautiful green space in Burnley that will become an all encompassing adult playground. As well as the music, it offers a considered collection of food, drink and gin and cocktail bars offering a wide range of mouthwatering treats to keep you fueled and the good times flowing. On top of that, you can expect immersive production and world class sound systems to really take every set to the next level.

faqs.question: What happens If I bought a ticket and cannot attend?
faqs.answer:
Unfortunately we can’t issue you with a refund if you can’t make the event due to work commitments or your mates have dropped out. In these circumstances, we advise passing on your tickets privately to avoid losing out on the money spent.

 

Refunds can only be offered if the event is cancelled or postponed, as agreed upon purchase.

faqs.question: When is Wile Out Festival 2023?
faqs.answer: Wile Out Festival 2023 takes place on Saturday 29th July 2023.

faqs.question: What is included in a VIP ticket?
faqs.answer: VIP tickets include access to VIP area, VIP toilets & bar, and queue jump.

faqs.question: Where is Wile Out Festival?
faqs.answer: Wile Out Festival is located at Towneley Park Burnley BB11 in Burnley.

faqs.question: Does Wile Out Festival have any age restrictions?
faqs.answer: Yes you must be 18 or over to attend Wile Out Festival. You may be asked to show photo ID.
